---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Dermatology — Program Requirements" description="ACD dermatology training program and assessment requirements.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Program Requirements</h1>
    <p>Dermatology — ACD · 4 years clinical training</p>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <h2>Workplace-Based Assessments</h2>
    <p>Trainees must complete the minimum number of WBAs each year:</p>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Case Based Discussions (CBD)</div>
      <p>Structured discussion of patient cases with a supervisor — covering diagnosis, management, and clinical reasoning.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Dermatology Clinical Evaluation Exercise (DCE)</div>
      <p>Direct observation of a clinical consultation including history, examination, and management plan.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Procedural Dermatology Assessment (PDA)</div>
      <p>Direct observation of procedural skills including skin surgery and other dermatological procedures.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <h2>Summative In-Training Assessments (SITAs)</h2>
    <p>Trainees must successfully complete SITAs as per their clinical rotation in order to progress in the training program. SITAs provide a formal summative judgement of overall clinical performance each rotation.</p>
  </div>
</Layout>
